1. fargate-task-execution-role -> Role ( + giving ECS permission to assume this role ) + Policy
        A. Create a role for the task execution role having a trust policy
                aws iam create-role `
                --role-name XpressBuy-Service-Execution-Role `
                --assume-role-policy-document file://C:/Users/.../ecs-service-assume-role-policy.json


        B. Make a new policy and attach it to the role
                aws iam put-role-policy `
                --policy-name XpressBuy-readAccess-systemsManager-parameterStore-policy `
                --role-name XpressBuy-Service-Execution-Role `
                --policy-document file://C:/Users/.../readAccess-systemsManager-parameterStore-policy.json




2. fargate-task-role -> Role ( + giving ECS permission to assume this role ) + Policy
        A. Create a role for the task role having a trust policy
                aws iam create-role `
                --role-name XpressBuy-task-Role `
                --assume-role-policy-document file://C:/Users/.../ecs-service-assume-role-policy.json

        B. Make a new policy and attach it to the role
                aws iam put-role-policy `
                // --policy-name SSM-access-Policy `
                --role-name XpressBuy-task-Role `
                --policy-document file://C:/Users/.../readAccess-systemsManager-parameterStore-policy.json

        C. Attach cloudwatch access policy (pre-defined) to the role
                aws iam attach-role-policy --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/CloudWatchFullAccess --role-name XpressBuy-task-Role

        D. Attach XRay read access policy (pre-defined) to the role
                aws iam attach-role-policy --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AWSXRayDaemonWriteAccess --role-name XpressBuy-task-Role